parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Water Ingress into Oil
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water leaking into the engine oil can cause catastrophic engine failure, leading to costly repairs, potential accidents, and stranded vehicles.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Oil Pan Failure due to Road Debris
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The aluminum oil pan is prone to damage from road debris, causing oil leaks and potentially leading to engine failure.
Premature engine failure can result in costly repairs, potential accidents, and stranded vehicles.
Failure of the cooling fan motor can cause engine overheating, leading to premature engine failure, reduced fuel efficiency, and decreased vehicle performance.
Failure of the alternator belt can cause battery drain, leading to engine stalling, reduced vehicle performance, and potential accidents.
The unintended acceleration of the vehicle in reverse gear can cause loss of control, accidents, and serious injuries to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The vehicle takes off at high speed without application of the accelerator pedal when shifted into reverse gear
resulting in loss of control and potential accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause a loss of braking power, leading to increased stopping distances, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal travels further than usual
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
